While it is possible that the UDC was involved in its creation, there is no direct evidence provided in the documents to support this claim.

mistral.reason: The Memorial to Women of the Confederacy was erected by a male Confederate veteran, not by the United Daughters of the Confederacy.

llama3.1.reason: The Memorial to Women of the Confederacy was actually created by a male Confederate veteran, not the United Daughters of the Confederacy, and it only honors mothers for raising their great Confederate soldier sons, which reduces the recognition of female work in the war.
